comments: They ask about the involvment of "hovercraft or any water borne craft" but not about sample size justification.
I could not find the form on their website withouth login credentials but I used a filled out form that I have found on google.

The form asked me to confirm if I follow the data protection standards of the university but has not asked specifically about any of the data management practices. However, their internal protocol included information on them.

"Explain what measures are in place to maintain confidentiality. This information must include: data storage (locked file cabinets/offices, password protection, etc.), data location and duration, description of persons with access to the data, and the method of destroying the data when completed." Do we consider this as a question about data archival?
"Explain how access to the data will be controlled and whether the access is logged." could we specify this as question about open data sharing?
"Where will data be stored when they are “at rest” (i.e., not in use)?" Would this be considered as a question about archival?
secondary data analysis. "Who will have access to the data? If any non-Duke researchers will have access to the data, please identify them." Would you consider this as an open data question?
asks about measures of risk minimizitation but that does not mean that it is a minimal risk IRB form
I rated this form as both minimal and non-minimal risk because this form could be used to get HIPAA waiwer. If this is correct my rating for uscd_01 should be changed as well.
the form states that confirmatory analyses should be registered but does not recommend registries.
minimal risk explicitely is only asked if prisoners are involved. not sure about data archival
